d 'MAKI': module to implement Maki (2012) cointegration test with unknown number of breaks
d
d	maki performs the residual-based cointegration test of Maki
d (2012), which allows the cointegrating relationship to have an   
d unknown number of structural breaks, smaller than or equal to a
d maximum number of breaks k set a priori.  The procedure   
d combines the sequential break-search idea of Bai and Perron
d (1998) with the unit-root testing strategy of Kapetanios (2005). 
d   The null hypothesis is no cointegration; the alternative is
d cointegration with i breaks (i {c <=} k). For each candidate set 
d   of breaks the test estimates the regression by OLS, runs an
d ADF-type regression on the residuals, and records the t-statistic
d    for the residual unit-root coefficient. The test statistic is
d the minimum t-statistic over all the partitions searched up to k 
d   breaks. Large negative values lead to rejection of the no-
d cointegration null. Breakpoints are selected by minimizing the
d sum	 of squared residuals (SSR).	This command is a
d Stata/Mata port of the original GAUSS procedures written by Daiki
d Maki and distributed in the TSPDLIB	 library (Aptech Systems).
d The first regressor in indepvars through the fourth is supported;
d critical values are available for    up to four regressors only. 
d
d KW: structural breaks
d KW: Maki
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260627
d
d Author: Ozan Eruygur,  Ankara Haci Bayram Veli University
d Support: email eruygur@@gmail.com
d
f maki.ado
f maki.sthlp
